definitions.definition: A simple aliphatic alcohol formally derived from ethane by replacing one hydrogen atom with a hydroxyl group: CH 3 -CH 2 -OH.
Specifically , this form of alcohol as a fuel .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) A simple aliphatic alcohol formally derived from ethane by replacing one hydrogen atom with a hydroxyl group: CH 3 -CH 2 -OH.
